.TH "EVI" "1" "<<<DATE>>>" "1" "Evi"

.SH NAME
.B evi
- the official Evi compiler



.SH SYNOPSIS
.B evi
.RB [OPTION...]
.RB file...



.SH DESCRIPTION
.B evi
is the official compiler for the Evi programming language. It is written in C++ by Sjoerd Vermeulen.





.SH OPTIONS

.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-c, --compile-only
Compile and assemble but do not link.
.UNINDENT

.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \--c-flags
Display the flags passed to the c compiler for linkage.
.UNINDENT

.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \--emit-llvm
Emit llvm IR instead of an executable.
.UNINDENT

.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-E
Preprocess only but do not compile or link.
.UNINDENT

.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \--generate-ast
Generate AST image (for debugging purposes).
.UNINDENT

.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-o, --output=OUTFILE
Output to OUTFILE instead of to standard output.
.UNINDENT

.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-v, --verbose
Produce verbose output.
.UNINDENT

.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-?, --help
Give a help list
.UNINDENT

.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \--usage
Give a short usage message
.UNINDENT

.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-V, --version
Print program version
.UNINDENT



.SH FILES
.TP
.I
/usr/share/man/man1/evi.1.gz
.TP
.I
/usr/share/bash-completion/completions/evi
.TP
.I
/usr/bin/evi



.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B
0
Success

.TP
.B
64
Invalid command line arguments

.TP
.B
65
Parse, type, codegen or output error


